{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "ops-success-2026-v1",
    "name": "OPS — ✅ SUCCESS Scenarios",
    "description": "Happy-path test suite for the Order Processing System.\n\n**Run order matters — requests are chained via collection variables:**\n1. Folder 1 (Authentication) — captures {{token}}\n2. Folder 2 (Order Placement) — captures {{order_id}} and {{customer_id}}\n3. Folder 3 (Order Retrieval) — uses {{order_id}}\n4. Folder 4 (Order Cancellation) — places + cancels a fresh order\n5. Folder 5 (Health Check) — no auth needed\n\n**Service ports:**\n- Order Service  →  http://localhost:8080\n- Inventory Service → http://localhost:8081 (Kafka only, no REST)\n- Notification Service → http://localhost:8082 (Kafka/SQS only, no REST)\n\n**Hardcoded users:**\n- user1 / password1  (ROLE_USER)\n- admin / admin123   (ROLE_ADMIN)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",               "value": "http://localhost:8080", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "token",                  "value": "",                      "type": "string", "description": "JWT — auto-set by Login request" },
    { "key": "order_id",               "value": "",                      "type": "string", "description": "Auto-set by Place Order Single Item" },
    { "key": "customer_id",            "value": "CUST001",               "type": "string" },
    { "key": "multi_order_id",         "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "cancel_order_id",        "value": "",                      "type": "string", "description": "Auto-set by Place Order To Cancel" },
    { "key": "idempotency_key",        "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "idempotency_key_multi",  "value": "",                      "type": "string" },
    { "key": "cancel_idempotency_key", "value": "",                      "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "1 · Authentication",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "01 · Login as Regular User  →  200 OK",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains JWT token', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('token');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', json.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token captured:', json.token.substring(0, 30) + '...');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('expiresIn is 86400000 (24 h)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().expiresIn).to.equal(86400000);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Content-Type is application/json', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type')).to.include('application/json');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"user1\",\n  \"password\": \"password1\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticates with user1/password1 (ROLE_USER). Captures the JWT into {{token}} for use in all subsequent protected requests.\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with {token, expiresIn:86400000}"
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "02 · Login as Admin  →  200 OK",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains JWT token (admin)', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('token');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('expiresIn is 86400000 (24 h)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().expiresIn).to.equal(86400000);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"admin\",\n  \"password\": \"admin123\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "auth", "login"]
            },
            "description": "Authenticates with admin/admin123 (ROLE_ADMIN). Verifies admin credentials work independently.\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with {token, expiresIn:86400000}\n\n**Note:** Does NOT overwrite {{token}} — token from request 01 remains active."
          }
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "2 · Order Placement",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "03 · Place Order — Single Item  →  201 Created",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Generate a fresh UUID as the idempotency key",
                  "const key = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idempotency_key', key);",
                  "console.log('Idempotency-Key set to:', key);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201 Created', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Order is returned with PENDING status', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('orderId');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.orderId).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.equal('PENDING');",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('order_id', json.orderId);",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('customer_id', json.customerId);",
                  "    console.log('Captured order_id:', json.orderId);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('customerId matches request', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().customerId).to.equal('CUST001');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('totalAmount is correct (qty 2 × price 49.99 = 99.98)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(parseFloat(pm.response.json().totalAmount)).to.be.closeTo(99.98, 0.01);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('items array has exactly 1 item', function () {",
                  "    const items = pm.response.json().items;",
                  "    pm.expect(items).to.be.an('array').with.lengthOf(1);",
                  "    pm.expect(items[0].productId).to.equal('PROD-001');",
                  "    pm.expect(items[0].quantity).to.equal(2);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('createdAt is present', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().createdAt).to.not.be.null;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('message is present', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",    "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization",   "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{idempotency_key}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"customerId\": \"CUST001\",\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"productId\": \"PROD-001\",\n      \"productName\": \"Wireless Headphones\",\n      \"quantity\": 2,\n      \"unitPrice\": 49.99\n    }\n  ]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders"]
            },
            "description": "Places a new order for customer CUST001 with a single product.\n\n**Pre-request:** Auto-generates a UUID as the Idempotency-Key header.\n**Post-test:** Captures {{order_id}} and {{customer_id}} for Folder 3 & 4.\n\n**Expected:**\n- 201 Created\n- status = PENDING\n- totalAmount = 99.98 (2 × 49.99)\n- 1 item in items array\n\n**Async behaviour:** Kafka publishes `order.created` → inventoryService checks stock → publishes `inventory.updated` → orderService updates status to CONFIRMED or FAILED. Use Folder 3 requests after a few seconds to see the updated status."
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "04 · Place Order — Multiple Items  →  201 Created",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const key = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('idempotency_key_multi', key);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201 Created', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Order placed for CUST002 with PENDING status', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.equal('PENDING');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.customerId).to.equal('CUST002');",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('multi_order_id', json.orderId);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('items array has exactly 3 items', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().items).to.be.an('array').with.lengthOf(3);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('totalAmount is correct (49.99 + 29.97 + 29.98 = 109.94)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(parseFloat(pm.response.json().totalAmount)).to.be.closeTo(109.94, 0.01);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Each item has required fields', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.json().items.forEach(function (item) {",
                  "        pm.expect(item).to.have.property('itemId');",
                  "        pm.expect(item).to.have.property('productId');",
                  "        pm.expect(item).to.have.property('quantity');",
                  "        pm.expect(item).to.have.property('unitPrice');",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",    "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization",   "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{idempotency_key_multi}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"customerId\": \"CUST002\",\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"productId\": \"PROD-001\",\n      \"productName\": \"Wireless Headphones\",\n      \"quantity\": 1,\n      \"unitPrice\": 49.99\n    },\n    {\n      \"productId\": \"PROD-002\",\n      \"productName\": \"USB-C Cable 2m\",\n      \"quantity\": 3,\n      \"unitPrice\": 9.99\n    },\n    {\n      \"productId\": \"PROD-003\",\n      \"productName\": \"Phone Stand\",\n      \"quantity\": 2,\n      \"unitPrice\": 14.99\n    }\n  ]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders"]
            },
            "description": "Places an order with 3 different products for CUST002.\n\n**Expected:**\n- 201 Created\n- 3 items in response\n- totalAmount = 109.94 (49.99 + 3×9.99 + 2×14.99)"
          }
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "3 · Order Retrieval",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "05 · Get Order by ID  →  200 OK",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('orderId matches the requested ID', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.orderId).to.equal(pm.collectionVariables.get('order_id'));",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has all required fields', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('orderId');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('customerId');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('totalAmount');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('items');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('createdAt');",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('status is a valid OrderStatus enum', function () {",
                  "    const validStatuses = ['PENDING', 'CONFIRMED', 'PROCESSING', 'SHIPPED', 'DELIVERED', 'CANCELLED', 'FAILED'];",
                  "    pm.expect(validStatuses).to.include(pm.response.json().status);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('items array is non-empty', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().items).to.be.an('array').and.not.empty;",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('totalAmount is positive', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(parseFloat(pm.response.json().totalAmount)).to.be.above(0);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/{{order_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "{{order_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Retrieves full order details for the order placed in request 03.\n\n**Depends on:** {{order_id}} captured from request 03.\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with complete OrderResponse.\n\n**Tip:** If run immediately after placing, status = PENDING. Run after a few seconds to see CONFIRMED (if inventory check succeeds) or FAILED."
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "06 · Get Order Status Only  →  200 OK (plain text)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response body is a valid OrderStatus string', function () {",
                  "    const body = pm.response.text().trim();",
                  "    const validStatuses = ['PENDING', 'CONFIRMED', 'PROCESSING', 'SHIPPED', 'DELIVERED', 'CANCELLED', 'FAILED'];",
                  "    pm.expect(validStatuses).to.include(body);",
                  "    console.log('Current order status:', body);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/{{order_id}}/status",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "{{order_id}}", "status"]
            },
            "description": "Returns ONLY the status string for an order — lightweight polling endpoint.\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK, plain-text response body such as `PENDING` or `CONFIRMED`.\n\n**Note:** This is a plain text response, not JSON."
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "07 · Get All Orders for Customer  →  200 OK (array)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response is a JSON array', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json).to.be.an('array');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Array has at least one order', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().length).to.be.at.least(1);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('All orders belong to CUST001', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.json().forEach(function (order) {",
                  "        pm.expect(order.customerId).to.equal('CUST001');",
                  "    });",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Each order has required fields', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.json().forEach(function (order) {",
                  "        pm.expect(order).to.have.property('orderId');",
                  "        pm.expect(order).to.have.property('status');",
                  "        pm.expect(order).to.have.property('totalAmount');",
                  "        pm.expect(order).to.have.property('items');",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/customer/CUST001",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "customer", "CUST001"]
            },
            "description": "Returns all orders for customer CUST001 (order from request 03 must exist).\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with a non-empty array of OrderResponse objects."
          }
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "4 · Order Cancellation",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "08 · Place Order (to be cancelled)  →  201 Created",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const key = pm.variables.replaceIn('{{$guid}}');",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('cancel_idempotency_key', key);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 201 Created', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Captures cancel_order_id for next request', function () {",
                  "    const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(json.status).to.equal('PENDING');",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('cancel_order_id', json.orderId);",
                  "    console.log('cancel_order_id set to:', json.orderId);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type",    "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization",   "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "{{cancel_idempotency_key}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"customerId\": \"CUST001\",\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"productId\": \"PROD-004\",\n      \"productName\": \"Laptop Stand\",\n      \"quantity\": 1,\n      \"unitPrice\": 29.99\n    }\n  ]\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders"]
            },
            "description": "Places a fresh order specifically to be cancelled in the next request.\n\n**IMPORTANT:** Cancel request (09) must be sent quickly — before the Kafka async flow changes status from PENDING to CONFIRMED. Once CONFIRMED, cancellation is rejected with 422."
          }
        },

        {
          "name": "09 · Cancel Order  →  204 No Content",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 204 No Content', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(204);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response body is empty', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.text()).to.be.empty;",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Authorization",  "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
              { "key": "X-Customer-Id", "value": "CUST001" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/{{cancel_order_id}}",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "{{cancel_order_id}}"]
            },
            "description": "Cancels the PENDING order created in request 08.\n\n**Required headers:**\n- `Authorization` — JWT Bearer token\n- `X-Customer-Id` — must match the customerId on the order\n\n**Expected:** 204 No Content, empty body.\n\n**Side effect:** Kafka publishes `order.cancelled` event → notificationService sends CANCELLED email."
          }
        }

      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "5 · Actuator / Health Check",
      "item": [

        {
          "name": "10 · Health Check  →  200 UP (no auth required)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status 200 OK', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Overall status is UP', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().status).to.equal('UP');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response has components', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json()).to.have.property('components');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/actuator/health",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Spring Boot Actuator health endpoint — publicly accessible without JWT.\n\n**Expected:** 200 OK with `{\"status\":\"UP\", \"components\":{...}}`\n\n**Checks:**  Postgres DB, Redis, Kafka, Disk Space, Ping"
          }
        }

      ]
    }

  ]
}
